title: 820-00426-A vcore present fan spin, chime, but not turning on
message:
This came in with massive thermal paste at cpu and gpu heatsink, clean it off, and i get the symptom like in the title, I have replaced 3 fdmf6708n new from mouser.. but still the same.. i got chime but no usb activity, fan spin will go loud after a while, but idk if its because the cpu itself is hot or because its the 'symptom'..-

title: 820-00426-A vcore present fan spin, chime, but not turning on
message: well, i see that pp3v3_S5 is shorted to ground at 18 ohm.. i never check pp3v3_s5 because I have fan spin, but do you think i have one before i flash this bios ? ( still have fan spin ) , or some bios flashing mechanic trigger a short on this line ?

title: 820-00426-A vcore present fan spin, chime, but not turning on
message:
BIOS cannot drop 3V3_S5.
18 ohm is very low and some component is damaged there.
Injection voltage doesn't help too much, unless you can check with a thermal camera.

title: 820-00426-A vcore present fan spin, chime, but not turning on

title: 820-00426-A vcore present fan spin, chime, but not turning on
message: NO, just be sure to have the same Intel marking code on it...
